Netflix Review Sentiment Analyzer

A Streamlit web app for analyzing IMDb-style reviews of Netflix shows and movies using TextBlob. Users can upload review datasets, write custom reviews, and explore sentiment trends through interactive visualizations.

Live Demo

Launch App
Replace with your deployed Streamlit Cloud URL.

Features

Upload CSV files with reviews and sentiments
Analyze custom reviews in real time
Auto-assigns show titles and years if missing
Visualizes:
Overall sentiment (bar chart)
Show-wise sentiment (pie chart)
Comparison between two shows (bar chart)
Dataset Format

Required columns:

review
sentiment (values: positive or negative)
Optional columns:

title
year
Missing values are filled with random Netflix titles and years.

How It Works

Sentiment detected using TextBlob polarity
Matplotlib used for charts
Neutral sentiment supported only for custom reviews
Dataset filtered to include only positive and negative
Installation

git clone https://github.com/your-username/netflix-review-sentiment.git
cd netflix-review-sentiment
pip install -r requirements.txt
streamlit run app.py
Download required corpora:

python -m textblob.download_corpora
Deployment

Push code to GitHub
Go to streamlit.io/cloud
Deploy with app.py as the main file
Requirements

streamlit==1.35.0
pandas==2.2.2
textblob==0.17.1
matplotlib==3.8.4
nltk==3.8.1
